25/06/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- The house of representatives passed a resolution late Monday (23 June) supporting the US-Adriatic Charter and the candidacies of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia for NATO membership.
The resolution commends efforts of the three countries to integrate into Euro-Atlantic structures and urges NATO to invite the three to join the alliance soon.
The United States and the three Balkan states signed the charter in Tirana on 2 May.
(MIA, HINA, A1 TV - 24/06/03)
